  \emph{(surj)} every element of \(M'\) equals \(s^{-1}\,g(m)\) for some \(s \in S\), \(m \in M\); and
  \emph{(exists\_of\_eq)} if \(g(m_1) = g(m_2)\) then \(s\,m_1 = s\,m_2\) for some \(s \in S\).
  Supplying these three fields constructs \(\mathrm{IsLocalizedModule}\,S\,g\).
\end{lemma}

